{"RUIN":[{"def":"The act of falling or tumbling down; fall.","pos":""},{"def":"Such a change of anything as destroys it, or entirely defeats its object, or unfits it for use; destruction; overthrow; as, the ruin of a ship or an army; the ruin of a constitution or a government; the ruin of health or hopes.","pos":""}],"RUINABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being ruined.","pos":""}],"RUINATE":[{"def":"To demolish; to subvert; to destroy; to reduce to poverty; to ruin.","pos":""},{"def":"To cause to fall; to cast down.","pos":""}],"RUINATION":[{"def":"The act of ruining, or the state of being ruined.","pos":""}],"RUINER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, ruins.","pos":""}],"RUINIFORM":[{"def":"Having the appearance of ruins, or of the ruins of houses; -- said of certain minerals.","pos":""}],"RUINOUS":[{"def":"Causing, or tending to cause, ruin; destructive; baneful; pernicious; as, a ruinous project.","pos":""},{"def":"Characterized by ruin; ruined; dilapidated; as, an edifice, bridge, or wall in a ruinous state.","pos":""}]}